(22, 'Launch & Growth Strategy', '<p>For your product launch, set clear goals and specify priorities. Share the goals with your team and other stakeholders then clearly define their roles and responsibilities. Develop a detailed launch plan. In your planning phase, define positioning, benefits, advantages, target markets, and metrics. Also, create a communication plan that will help everyone understand the vison, positioning and the product&rsquo;s story.</p>\r\n<p>There are a number of websites where you can list your startup. See http://promotehour.com/. The following is a sample list.</p>\r\n<p>Betalist.com - 25,000+ early adopters, $129 to post</p>\r\n<p>Erlibird.com - 40,000+ beta testers, $149 to post</p>\r\n<p>KillerStartups.com - 5,000 potential users, $169 to post</p>\r\n<p>Hakernews - https://news.ycombinator.com/</p>\r\n<p>Smart Insights proposes an 11 step launch marketing plan for Startups.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.smartinsights.com/marketing-planning/create-a-marketing-plan/10-nov-start-marketing-plan/" target="_blank">http://www.smartinsights.com/marketing-planning/create-a-marketing-plan/10-nov-start-marketing-plan/</a></p>\r\n<p>The key steps in their product launch framework include:</p>\r\n<p>Phase 1</p>\r\n<p>1. Strategic Positioning &ndash; Determine how to express and leverage your value proposition that will position your offering with your initial target market which should be the early adopters.</p>\r\n<p>2. Brand Development &ndash; Branding helps you stand out from the crowd. Register a domain name, apply for a trademark for both your company&rsquo;s name and for a tag line that conveys your value proposition. Also, create an attractive logo. However, all components of your marketing plan should be consistent with your brand strategy.</p>\r\n<p>3. Web Presence &ndash; Your smartphone app and web site are your primary point of contact with most of your stakeholders. These will support your offering or supplement your offering, so usability, availability and utility are critical. Ensure your app and web site have the quality that matches your brand image.</p>\r\n<p>Phase 2</p>\r\n<p>4. Blog Strategy &ndash; Your social marketing and communications strategy should include a blog that enhances your strategic positioning. It should be very professional and well managed. You need a clear editorial strategy and the resources to execute that strategy. The content must be carefully planned and produced. It should support your brand position, highlight product benefits, be informative, and convey thought leadership.</p>\r\n<p>5. Digital PR and Partnering &ndash; You need a digital PR and partnering campaign to supplement your social media activities. While the main goals are to drive traffic, convert customers and generate revenues, you must also monitor word of mouth and your online reputation. You have to master modern PR techniques that include viral communications, crowdsourcing, community development and word of mouth.</p>\r\n<p>6. Viral Videos and Guerilla Marketing &ndash; Viral videos and guerilla marketing demand creativity, original content and quality production.</p>\r\n<p>7. SEO and Link Building &ndash; You need an effective SEO strategy to support your web presence, blog, digital PR and social media marketing activities.</p>\r\n<p>Phase 3</p>\r\n<p>8. Online Advertising &ndash; Social media platforms like Facebook, allow you to market to very specific market segments. You need a very well planned campaign that uses key metrics to track the effectiveness of each activity.</p>\r\n<p>9. Strategic PR &ndash; Content marketing activities can drive high profile awareness and word of mouth promotion. High impact events can supplement this approach but is most effective if you have brand awareness. 10. Crowdsourcing Campaigns &ndash; Tap into the power of the crowd by running contest-based campaigns and by developing and executing viral content.</p>\r\n<p>11. Speaking and Briefing &ndash; Cultivate a thought leadership reputation in your industry. You can then execute a highly targeted speaking and media briefing program.</p>\r\n<p>According to Balaji Viswanathan, your launch strategy should include the following:</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://www.quora.com/How-do-you-successfully-launch-a-product/answer/Balaji-Viswanathan-2?srid=CRHx" target="_blank">https://www.quora.com/How-do-you-successfully-launch-a-product/answer/Balaji-Viswanathan-2?srid=CRHx</a></p>\r\n<p>Six months before your launch you should post content on twitter and other social media platforms, get active on forums, setup you blog, and sign up a few influential customers to participate in UAT.</p>\r\n<p>Three months before launch cultivate relationships with bloggers and start attending related events. Also list your startup on Angel List, StartupLi.st CrunchBase and Listio.</p>\r\n<p>One week before launch build a great landing page, optimize your app and website, fine tune your SEO, use social monitoring tools, write a press release, setup your Facebook page, create viral content with emotive stories, create interesting infographics, create fun contests, write to bloggers, prepare a video demo, and create a presentation that summarizes the problem, solution, benefits and advantages.</p>\r\n<p>On your launch day, post to your blog your presentation, videos and testimonials from UAT testers. Tweet, post on Facebook, send emails, with a call to action. Post your site in killerstartups, hackernews and similar web sites. Monitor social media and your site&rsquo;s metrics. Respond to queries as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p>After the launch, thank bloggers and others who covered you. Engage customers on social media. Fix bugs and develop a roadmap for new features. Write &ldquo;how to&rdquo; tutorials and leverage opportunities to demo your product.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../../../images/setup-operation1.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="452" /></p>\r\n<p>Source: RocketWatcher.com</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://blog.gleam.io/prelaunch/" target="_blank">https://blog.gleam.io/prelaunch/</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://venturebeat.com/2013/06/05/the-ultimate-guide-to-startup-pre-launch-marketing-in-5-simple-steps/" target="_blank">http://venturebeat.com/2013/06/05/the-ultimate-guide-to-startup-pre-launch-marketing-in-5-simple-steps/</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://foundrmag.com/pr-checklist-for-startups-15-things-to-do-before-your-product-launch/" target="_blank">https://foundrmag.com/pr-checklist-for-startups-15-things-to-do-before-your-product-launch/</a></p>', 'R3', '#58c517', '1485168966_525278220.0 CBS Launch Strategy Blank.pdf', '1485168966_527838220.0 Launch Strategy Template.pdf', 1, '2016-09-08 06:41:33'),
